@startuml cgs-junior-overview
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CGS FOR JUNIORS — "The Post Office Analogy"
'  Simple overview: What is CGS and how does a message flow?
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **What is CGS?**\nCGS is like a **post office** for software applications.\nApps don't talk to each other directly — they all send messages through CGS,\nwhich figures out **who** should receive it, **translates** it if needed, and **delivers** it.

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 60
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam padding 8

' === WHO SENDS MESSAGES? ===
package "**Who sends messages?**\n(173 registered applications)" as senders #F1F8E9 {

  component "**Tax & Property**\nCBB, CIN, CKD, CMD\nCGA, CBR, CZA" as tax_apps #DCEDC8
  
  component "**Citizen Services**\niBurgerzaken\nPortal / KCC\nFrontOffice" as citizen_apps #DCEDC8
  
  component "**Internal Systems**\nCMG (Broker)\nCML (National)\nCiPers (Personnel)" as internal_apps #DCEDC8
  
  component "**External Partners**\nSquitXO, Corsa\nAlfresco, Decos\nBuitenBeter, JCC" as external_apps #DCEDC8
}

' === CGS — THE POST OFFICE ===
package "    " as cgs_box #E3F2FD {
  
  component "          **CGS — The Post Office**\n\n          //173 apps · 218 services · 660 authorizations//\n          //376 routing channels · 993 format translations//" as cgs_title #BBDEFB

  component "**1. Are you allowed?**\nCheck if the sender app\nis authorized for this service\n//(serviceusage table: 660 rules)//" as step1 #E3F2FD
  
  component "**2. What is this message?**\nIdentify the message type\nby namespace, key, or content\n//(messagedefinition: 2065 types)//" as step2 #E3F2FD
  
  component "**3. Translate if needed**\nConvert between formats\nso receiver understands it\n//(transformationdefinition: 993 XSLTs)//" as step3 #E3F2FD
  
  component "**4. Route to receiver(s)**\nFind which app(s) should\nget this message\n//(channeldefinition: 376 routes)//" as step4 #E3F2FD
  
  component "**5. Deliver**\nSend via the right protocol\n(SOAP, ABAP, Java, ebMS...)\n//(adapterdefinition: 10 protocols)//" as step5 #E3F2FD

  step1 -right-> step2
  step2 -right-> step3
  step3 -down-> step4
  step4 -left-> step5
}

' === WHO RECEIVES MESSAGES? ===
package "**Who receives messages?**\n(providers / destinations)" as receivers #FFF3E0 {

  component "**CiVision SAP Apps**\nCBB, CGA, CZA, CIN\n(via ABAP protocol)" as sap_recv #FFE0B2
  
  component "**Broker Systems**\nCMG, CML, CMM, CMZ\n(via Java protocol)" as broker_recv #FFE0B2
  
  component "**Document Systems**\nAlfresco, Corsa, Decos\n(via CMIS protocol)" as dms_recv #FFE0B2
  
  component "**National Government**\nBRP, GBA-V, BV-BSN\nKadaster, LV WOZ, KVK\n(via Digikoppeling)" as national_recv #FFE0B2
}

' === CONNECTIONS ===
tax_apps -[#558B2F,bold]-> step1
citizen_apps -[#558B2F,bold]-> step1
internal_apps -[#558B2F,bold]-> step1
external_apps -[#558B2F,bold]-> step1

step5 -[#E65100,bold]-> sap_recv
step5 -[#E65100,bold]-> broker_recv
step5 -[#E65100,bold]-> dms_recv
step5 -[#E65100,bold]-> national_recv

@enduml


@startuml cgs-junior-sync-vs-async
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CGS FOR JUNIORS — Synchronous vs Asynchronous
'  "The two ways CGS delivers messages"
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **The Two Ways CGS Delivers Messages**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam activityBorderColor #37474F
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #FFFFFF

|#E8F5E9| **SYNCHRONOUS (184 services)** — "I'll wait for the answer" |
start

:App sends a **question**
""Example: "Give me the address of citizen X"  "";

:CGS finds the right provider
and forwards the question;

:Provider answers **immediately**;

:CGS sends the answer
back to the app;

:App receives the answer
  ✅ Done!;
stop

|#FCE4EC| **ASYNCHRONOUS (34 services)** — "Just make sure everyone gets it" |
start

:App sends a **notification**
""Example: "Citizen X has moved to a new address"  "";

:CGS immediately confirms receipt
//"OK, I got it"  (Bv04Bericht)//;

:CGS looks up ALL apps that
need to know about this;
note right
  Example: **StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG**
  has **29 routing channels**
  delivering to **17 different apps**!
  
  Every app that cares about
  address changes gets a copy.
end note

fork
  :Send copy to **CBB** (taxes);
fork again
  :Send copy to **CGA** (addresses);
fork again
  :Send copy to **CMG** (broker);
fork again
  :Send copy to **CWIZ** (social);
fork again
  :Send copies to\n**13 more apps...**;
end fork

:All providers got their copy
  ✅ Done!;
stop

@enduml


@startuml cgs-junior-real-example
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CGS FOR JUNIORS — A Real Example
'  "Follow one message from start to finish"
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **Follow a Real Message: "A citizen moves to a new address"**\nThis is the most common flow in CGS (StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG — 29 channels)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "Municipal\nEmployee" as user
participant "iBurgerzaken\n//front-end app//" as ibz #C8E6C9
box "CGS Service Bus" #E3F2FD
  participant "Authorization" as auth #BBDEFB
  participant "Message\nMatching" as match #BBDEFB
  participant "Transformation\nEngine" as transform #BBDEFB
  participant "Router" as router #90CAF9
  participant "Delivery" as deliver #90CAF9
end box
participant "CBB\n//taxes//" as cbb #FFE0B2
participant "CGA\n//addresses//" as cga #FFE0B2
participant "CMG\n//broker//" as cmg #FFF9C4
participant "14 more\napps..." as others #E0E0E0

== Step 1: Employee registers the move ==

user -> ibz : Registers that citizen\nX moved from A to B

== Step 2: iBurgerzaken notifies CGS ==

ibz -> auth : SOAP message:\n"kennisgevingsBericht"\n(StUF-BG notification)
note right of auth
  ""<namespace>http://www.egem.nl/""
  ""  StUF/sector/bg/0204</namespace>""
  ""<messagekey>kennisgevingsBericht""
  ""</messagekey>""
end note

== Step 3: CGS processes the message ==

auth -> auth : Is iBurgerzaken allowed\nto call this service?\n✅ Yes (found in serviceusage)
auth --> ibz : "Message received" (Bv04)
note right: Async = immediate\nconfirmation.\niBurgerzaken\ncan continue working.

auth -> match : Forward message
match -> match : What type of message?\nMatch by namespace + key\n→ It's a BG kennisgeving!

match -> transform : Message matched
transform -> transform : Does anyone need\na different format?\n\nCBB speaks StUF **0204** ✅\nCGA speaks StUF **0204** ✅\nCWIZ speaks StUF **0210** ⚠️\n→ Transform 0204→0210 for CWIZ

transform -> router : Original + transformed copies

== Step 4: CGS delivers to ALL registered receivers ==

router -> router : Find all channels for\nStUFOntvangAsynchroonBG\n→ **29 channels found!**

router -> deliver : Route to each channel
deliver -> cbb : Copy 1 (StUF 0204)\nvia **ABAP** protocol
deliver -> cga : Copy 2 (StUF 0204)\nvia **ABAP** protocol
deliver -> cmg : Copy 3 (StUF 0204)\nvia **Java** protocol
deliver -> others : Copies 4-17\neach via its own\nprotocol & format

== Step 5: Each app processes independently ==

cbb -> cbb : Update tax records\nfor new address
cga -> cga : Update address\nregistration
cmg -> cmg : Update broker\ndata store
others -> others : Each does their\nown thing

note over auth, deliver
  **Why this matters:**
  Without CGS, iBurgerzaken would need to know about ALL 17 apps,
  speak ALL their protocols, and handle ALL their formats.
  
  With CGS, iBurgerzaken just sends ONE message in ONE format,
  and CGS takes care of the rest. If a new app joins tomorrow,
  you just add a channel — zero code changes in iBurgerzaken.
end note

@enduml


@startuml cgs-junior-message-types
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CGS FOR JUNIORS — Message Types Simplified
'  "The 4 kinds of messages"
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **The 4 Kinds of Messages in CGS**\n//Every message is one of these types//

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "**1. REQUEST** — Asking a question" as req_pkg #E8F5E9 {
  component "**vraagBericht**\n//\"question message\"//\n\n\"Give me the data of citizen 12345\"\n\"What is the WOZ value of this house?\"\n\"Find all cases for this person\"\n\nUsed **471 times** as the most\ncommon request type" as req #C8E6C9
}

package "**2. RESPONSE** — The answer" as resp_pkg #E3F2FD {
  component "**antwoordBericht**\n//\"answer message\"//\n\n\"Here is the data you asked for\"\n\n**synchroonAntwoordBericht** (258×)\nfor synchronous services\n\n**Bv03Bericht** (893×)\nfor async confirmations" as resp #BBDEFB
}

package "**3. NOTIFICATION** — Telling everyone about a change" as notif_pkg #FFF3E0 {
  component "**kennisgevingsBericht**\n//\"notification message\"//\n\n\"Citizen X has moved\"\n\"A new case was created\"\n\"Property value changed\"\n\nUsed **354 times** — triggers\nfan-out to many receivers" as notif #FFE0B2
}

package "**4. FAULT** — Something went wrong" as fault_pkg #FFEBEE {
  component "**Fo03Bericht / foutBericht**\n//\"error message\"//\n\n\"Service not found\"\n\"You are not authorized\"\n\"Invalid message format\"\n\n**Fo03 is #1 most configured**\n**message (2431×)** — every\nservice must know how\nto report errors" as fault #FFCDD2
}

req -[hidden]right-> resp
notif -[hidden]right-> fault

note bottom
  **The flow:**
  App sends REQUEST or NOTIFICATION →
  CGS processes it →
  Returns RESPONSE (success) or FAULT (error)
end note

@enduml


